  "articleSummary": "**Summary**\n\n\"Into the Breach\" is a technical analysis and defensive guide addressing the evolving landscape of supply chain attacks and developer-targeted exploits. The article argues that modern developer environments have become \"credential warehouses\" where local convenience creates catastrophic security risks, rendering traditional \"be careful\" advice obsolete. Using a proactive and prescriptive tone, the author advocates for a \"defense-in-depth\" strategy centered on filesystem isolation (DevContainers), strict secret scoping, and the aggressive deployment of \"Canarytokens\" (digital tripwires). The intended audience is software engineers and DevOps professionals who must shift from a model of human vigilance to one of automated boundaries and architectural isolation.",
